<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 17 at 3:28AM CDT until May 17 at 3:45AM CDT by NWS Wichita</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 345 AM CDT
FOR CENTRAL HARPER COUNTY...
At 328 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Anthony, moving
northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.
Locations impacted include...
Anthony, Harper and Danville.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;50 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
